'''''The New Jedi Order: Dark Journey''''', the tenth book in the [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|''New Jedi Order'']] series, is a novel by [[Elaine Cunningham]], published on [[January 29]], [[2002]] in paperback by [[Del Rey]]. It contained an excerpt of ''[[The Approaching Storm]]''. The [[Science Fiction Book Club]] also published an exclusive hardcover edition.

==Publisher's summary==
'''The New Jedi Order continues as Jaina Solo struggles with anger and despair after the Jedi Knights' harrowing adventure behind enemy lines.'''

''Though the Jedi strike force completed its deadly mission into Yuuzhan Vong territory, the price of success was tragedy: not everyone made it out alive. In a daring getaway, hotshot pilot Jaina Solo stole an enemy ship, taking along her fellow survivors&mdash;and leaving behind a huge piece of her heart.''

''With the enemy in hot pursuit, Jaina is forced to seek haven in the unprotected, unfriendly Hapes Cluster, where the Jedi are held responsible for a past tragedy&mdash;and where the royal family has grim plans for their famous Jedi guest. Even more sinister are the intentions of the Yuuzhan Vong, desperate to capture Jaina for a hideous sacrifice.''

''Grief-stricken and obsessed with revenge, Jaina is blind to these threats&mdash;and to the overpowering evil dangerously close to consuming her. In the coming conflagration, Jaina will be fighting not for victory or vengeance, but for her very being&hellip;''

==Plot summary==
Taking place just after ''[[The New Jedi Order: Star by Star]]'', [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] and the rest of the survivors from the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Myrkr/Legends|Myrkr]] [[Myrkr strike team|strike team]], including [[Lowbacca]], [[Zekk]], [[Ganner Rhysode]], [[Tenel Ka Djo]], [[Tahiri Veila]], [[Tekli]], [[Alema Rar]], and [[Tesar Sebatyne]], escape the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Koros-Strohna|worldship]] [[Baanu Rass|they were sent to]] in order to [[Mission to Myrkr|destroy the voxyn]], [[Voxyn|Jedi hunters created by the Vong]], by escaping in Executor [[Nom Anor]]'s ship, the [[Trickster|''Ksstarr'']]. Along the way, Jaina's oldest brother, [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]], was captured by the Vong and his execution is delayed until Jaina could be kidnapped, due to how much the Vong take it seriously for twins to fight to the death in their culture. The survivors take the body of Jaina's youngest brother, [[Anakin Solo|Anakin]], so he can have a proper funeral.

Meanwhile, back at [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and the Yuuzhan Vong are still fighting, and during [[Battle of Coruscant (Yuuzhan Vong War)|the battle]], [[Kyp Durron]]'s [[Kyp's Dozen|X-wing squadron]] and the ''Ksstarr'' join the fray. When the battle is lost to the Republic, the survivors of that battle, including Kyp, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Mara Jade Skywalker]], along with the ''Ksstarr'', all escape the captured New Republic capital [[Planet/Legends|planet]].

The survivors from the battle escape to the [[Hapes Cluster/Legends|Hapes Cluster]], which had lost its major Fleet in the [[Battle of Fondor|Battle]] of [[Fondor/Legends|Fondor]] [[25 ABY/Legends|nearly two years before]] in [[Yuuzhan Vong War|the war against the Yuuzhan Vong]] and is still recovering. The Cluster is now opening itself to refugees in the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], and on [[Hapes/Legends|Hapes]] itself, Prince [[Isolder]] has had several assassination attempts on him due to his leading of their loss at Fondor. Queen [[Teneniel Djo]] of Hapes is losing her will to live because of the loss of her unborn child during the Battle of Fondor, and former queen mother [[Ta'a Chume]] is seeking a replacement for Djo. As for the survivors of the strike team, they all feel through [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] that Jacen Solo is now dead from the Yuuzhan Vong, except for Leia, who is certain that Jacen is still alive, and Jaina, who also strangely did not feel her twin's death. Jaina suspects that her anger and rage over Anakin's death had distracted her sense of Jacen, though she now cares very little of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]]. Her reasoning is that because the Jedi and the New Republic dithered during the war, she finds that this has caused very little action in comparison to what all of the Jedi and Republic could have done had they not had, in Jaina's opinion, nonsense arguments over the matters of the war.

Jaina finally begins to understand the ''Ksstarr'' with Lowbacca and contacts [[Warmaster]] [[Tsavong Lah]] of the Yuuzhan Vong. She discovers the frigate's nature, she realizes it is in tribute to [[Yun-Harla]], the Trickster goddess of the Vong, since Nom Anor worships Yun-Harla. In an attempt to mock the Vong, Jaina renames the ''Ksstarr'' the ''Trickster'' after Yun-Harla's nature and how Eminence [[Harrar]] and [[Khalee Lah]] relates her deceptive talents with Yun-Harla. This would be considered blasphemy among the Yuuzhan Vong's culture if Harrar took this consideration seriously, and may even lead to his dishonorable execution. When the ''Trickster'' finally arrives on Hapes, Anakin is cremated and Jaina and Lowbacca begin to find ways to scramble the ''Trickster'' 's location.

Ta'a Chume, seeing how much of a warrior Jaina is, plans to have Jaina marry Isolder so she can lead Hapes to war against the Yuuzhan Vong. Since Tenenial Djo is too weak to lead Hapes into war against the Yuuzhan Vong and Chume's own granddaughter, Tenel Ka, pledges her allegiance more to the Jedi than to Hapes, Jaina seems to be the proper candidate for queen mother of Hapes. During all this, [[Jagged Fel]] of the [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] Fleet arrives at Hapes to support the New Republic after his failure at the [[Battle of Ithor]] early in the war. Kyp Durron becomes a member of Jag's fleet and in order to understand him more, Jaina becomes Kyp's apprentice, despite her disregard for him [[The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory II: Rebirth|prior to the fall of Coruscant]]. In the end, Tenenial Djo dies from poisoning thanks to Ta'a Chume's machinations, and despite the former Queen Mother's attempts, Jaina refuses to become the next queen mother of Hapes. Ta'a Chume's granddaughter, Tenel Ka, becomes the new queen. Jaina's attempts at scrambling the ''Trickster'' 's location succeeds in defeating the Vong twice when [[Battle of Hapes (Yuuzhan Vong War)|Hapes is pitted against them]], and even results in Khalee Lah committing suicide out of humiliation.

==Continuity==
The novel states that Tenel Ka "held her mother's hands in both of hers." However, Tenel Ka lost one arm in ''[[Young Jedi Knights: Lightsabers]]''. At one point, the floor of the ''Trickster'' is described as duracrete. However, Yuuzhan Vong vessels are made out of living beings and do not use inorganic materials.

